  "extraHighlightWords": [],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Monday, and our whole class had to line up outside the nurse's office for the yearly health check-up.",
      "zh": "星期一，我們全班都要在保健室外面排隊做年度健康檢查。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The nurse measured our height first, and I grew two whole centimeters since last year, which made me very happy.",
      "zh": "護士先量身高，我比去年長高了整整兩公分，這讓我非常開心。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice complained that her height had not changed at all, and she blamed it directly on not drinking enough milk.",
      "zh": "Bernice 抱怨她的身高完全沒變，直接怪罪是自己牛奶喝得不夠。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Next, the nurse checked our eyes, ears, nose, and throat, one student at a time, very quickly.",
      "zh": "接著護士檢查我們的眼睛、耳朵、鼻子和喉嚨，一次一個學生，速度很快。"
    },
    {
      "en": "She shined a small light into my ear and said everything looked completely healthy, which was a relief.",
      "zh": "她用一支小燈照進我的耳朵，說一切看起來都很健康，我聽了鬆了一口氣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "When it was William's turn at his own school, he apparently told the nurse his heart sounded like a robot engine.",
      "zh": "輪到 William 在他學校檢查的時候，他竟然跟護士說他的心臟聽起來像機器人引擎的聲音。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The nurse laughed and told him hearts are supposed to sound steady, not like a machine, but she admitted it was a creative idea.",
      "zh": "護士笑了，跟他說心臟應該要跳得穩定，不是像機器一樣，但她也承認這想法蠻有創意的。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Back at my school, the nurse also checked our teeth, and I have zero cavities this year, which felt like a small victory.",
      "zh": "回到我的學校，護士也檢查了我們的牙齒，我今年零蛀牙，感覺像是個小小的勝利。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice was not so lucky; the nurse told her she needs to see a real doctor about one tooth in the back of her mouth.",
      "zh": "Bernice 就沒那麼幸運了；護士跟她說她嘴巴後面有一顆牙齒需要去看真正的牙醫。"
    },
    {
      "en": "After teeth, we had to bend our arms, legs, and knees so the nurse could check how well our joints moved.",
      "zh": "檢查完牙齒後，我們要彎手臂、彎腿、彎膝蓋，讓護士檢查關節活動得好不好。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I could touch my toes without bending my knees at all, which made Bernice immediately try to copy me and fail.",
      "zh": "我可以不彎膝蓋就摸到腳趾，這讓 Bernice 馬上想模仿我，結果失敗了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The nurse also asked each of us a few quick questions, like whether we ever get headaches or feel sick after lunch.",
      "zh": "護士也問了我們幾個簡單的問題，像是會不會頭痛，或是吃完午餐後會不會不舒服。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I mentioned that I sometimes get a small headache after reading for too long, and she suggested taking breaks for my eyes.",
      "zh": "我提到有時候讀書讀太久會有點頭痛，她建議我應該讓眼睛多休息一下。"
    },
    {
      "en": "At the end, the nurse gave every student a small card listing our height, and a short note about our general health.",
      "zh": "最後，護士給每個學生一張小卡片，上面寫著身高，還有簡短的健康狀況記錄。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mine said \"healthy, active, good posture,\" which I plan to show to my whole family tonight like a report card.",
      "zh": "我的卡片上寫著「健康、活潑、姿勢良好」，我打算今晚像成績單一樣拿給全家人看。"
    },
    {
      "en": "On the walk home, I told Bernice that going to the hospital for a small tooth problem is not actually scary at all.",
      "zh": "回家路上，我跟 Bernice 說為了一顆小牙齒問題去醫院其實一點都不可怕。"
    },
    {
      "en": "She said she was not scared of the hospital, she was scared of the medicine they might give her afterward.",
      "zh": "她說她不是怕醫院，她是怕之後可能要吃的藥。"
    },
    {
      "en": "At home, Sophia looked at my little health card and said good health starts with good sleep, good food, and less phone time.",
      "zh": "回到家，Sophia 看了我那張小小的健康卡，說良好的健康始於充足的睡眠、健康的飲食，還有少滑手機。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William proudly showed his own health card too, though his said something about needing to sit still more during class.",
      "zh": "William 也驕傲地拿出他自己的健康卡，雖然上面寫的是上課時需要多坐好一點。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Perry, who has never had an official health check-up in his life, seemed perfectly healthy anyway, mostly from chasing his own tail all evening.",
      "zh": "Perry 這輩子從來沒做過正式的健康檢查，但看起來還是很健康，主要是因為他整個晚上都在追自己的尾巴。"
    }
  ],
